{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"df2a1532-3921-494a-b22e-a18e7b2eb4a3","content":"You're on MSTest 3.8.2, which supports the modern approach. Here's the recommended pattern:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests : IDisposable, IAsyncDisposable\n{\n    // TestContext is injected automatically via property\n    public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }\n\n    // Synchronous initialization — use the constructor\n    public MyTests()\n    {\n        // sync setup here\n    }\n\n    // Asynchronous initialization — use [TestInitialize]\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        // async setup here (runs before each test)\n    }\n\n    // Cleanup\n    public void Dispose() { /* sync cleanup */ }\n    public ValueTask DisposeAsync() { /* async cleanup */ }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task MyTest() { /* ... */ }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **Constructor** → synchronous per-test init\n- **`[TestInitialize]`** → async per-test init (runs after constructor)\n- **`TestContext`** → declared as a public settable property; MSTest injects it automatically before `[TestInitialize]` runs\n- **`[ClassInitialize]`/`[ClassCleanup]`** → for one-time per-class setup (static methods)\n- **`IAsyncDisposable`** → preferred for async cleanup over `[TestCleanup]`","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"462642dd-2269-48e8-bf0a-c1330b3d77e8","outputTokens":342,"requestId":"BC4C:1129F2:1E65C6D:21A2D6B:69FA9769"},"id":"cfb355a8-5caf-48c3-b3c4-51097b003ca8","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:20:49.881Z","parentId":"7ef62ab6-0892-4332-abee-e594ca7b05de"}
